<p><i>Director of Human Resources and Communications</i></p>
<p>Wahyudin Saptari Adikusumah joined PT AXIS Telekom Indonesia as the Director Human Resources (HR) effective December 1, 2007, responsible for the overall human resources aspects of the company. Before joining AXIS, Wahyudin Saptari Adikusumah spent almost five years as the HR Director of PT Perfetti Van Melle Indonesia (PVMI) an FMCG (confectionary), whereby he was responsible for setting up HR strategy and policies just after the merger of this company. PVMI employs 1500 people in two manufacturing sites and six regional sales offices through out Indonesia.</p>
<p>Prior to PVMI, Wahyudin Saptari Adikusumah has worked for more than 9 years with PT BHP Steel Indonesia (currently Bluescope Steel Indonesia). He started there in 1994 as the Vice President (VP) HR and Administration. In 1998, he was assigned as the VP Logistic, responsible for supply chain and customer service aspects whereby, through various projects, important savings were obtained. After this position, he became the VP HR and External Affairs, with the emphasis on human resources, community development and external relations, mainly with government network (regulatory).</p>
<p>During his service with PT BHP Steel Indonesia, he was also an active member of the Indonesia Chambers of Commerce - Banten, Executive Board of Banten International Business Association, Chairman of the Company Association in Krakatau Industrial Estate Cilegon and Secretary General of Indonesia Galvanized Companies Association (Gapsi). Prior to BHP Steel Indonesia, Wahyudin Saptari Adikusumah worked for Asahimas Subentra Chemicals (ASC) from 1989 until 1994 as the Personnel and Administration Manager. Wahyudin Saptari Adikusumah graduated from Economy Faculty, Krisnadwipayana University in Jakarta, Indonesia and holds several professional accreditations on HR management.</p></td>
